              <p> <span class="style2">As our focus in this issue is on the interplay between standard setting and the implementation of government policy, we begin this month&rsquo;s selection of news items and commentary with a range of stories that illustrate the various ways in which Europe and countries in Asia are making an impact in the standards arena, in large part as a result of the greater degree of coordination between their standards sector and the government. </span></p>
