                  <td colspan="2"><p> <strong><em> <strong><em> <strong><em>                  <strong><em> The answer lies in the &quot;O3 zone:&quot; open source, open standards and open systems</em></strong><em> &nbsp;&nbsp;[July 22, 2005]</em> </em></strong></em></strong></em></strong></p></td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="style2">
                  <td width="200" height="30"><p>&nbsp; </p></td>
                  <td width="333"><p> Guy Cross, Oracle director, Business Development, Oracle Asia Pacific Linux Business Unit, on what vendors are rallying behind<a href="http://www.techworld.com/applications/news/index.cfm?NewsID=4082"> ...Full Story</a> </p></td>
